      • readroot

        protected org.corfudb.runtime.collections.CDBPhysicalBTree.Node<K,V> readroot()
        read the root of the tree Note, this has the effect of inserting the tree container object into the read set, but does not put the actual node there. If query_helper returns false, it means we've already read the tree root in the current transaction, so we're forced to return the most recently observed value.
        Returns:
